rComments: His section (renal) is kind of heavy, but he explains concepts slowly and clearly. Sometimes he goes too far ahead, so it can be confusing sometimes in the middle lectures, but by the end it all comes together.
He is a very good lecturer. He repeats important parts of the lecture. Gives you FOOD! He is awesome.

Okay. Takes the EASIEST SECTION OF PSL301 and totally screws it with his, "sensorium" of jargon. e.g. instead of saying: they inject bicarbonate into the blood as a result of end stage kidney failure. scholey: They will permeate the blood compartment of the patient, and use hemodyalisis to readily diffuse a bicarbonate rich solution into the blood.

He is a clearly a master of his field, evidenced by the fact that he can talk without breaks for great length. This, however, does not make him a great lecturer. Leaves no time to gather thoughts; while we're writing he forges ahead like Lewis and Clarke. Speaks rather slowly but feels really quick oddly. Very odd pacing. Nice guy though.

He is on topic, but talks non-stop, without significant pause.  This leaves you no time to gather your thoughts about what he's just said, which snowballs into me getting lost. Also, the textbook and his notes are in different order. Why he shuffled them I don't know, but this makes me SUPER ******* MAD since I'm very ordered centric. Otherwise meh
Amazing prof! Great Pace and very easy to understand. His lectures are very well put together and easy to follow along with.
Amazing Prof, extremely clear, and has passion for what he is teaching
